^ Silver, Nate. 『Robopolls' Significantly More Favorable to Republicans Than Traditional Surveys. The New York Times. 28 October 2010. 
^ Schwartz, L. M.; Woloshin, S. On the Prevention and Treatment of Exaggeration. Journal of General Internal Medicine. 2003, 18 (2): 153–154. PMC 1494822. PMID 12542591. doi:10.1046/j.1525-1497.2003.21216.x.  編輯
^ Gaia Vince. Large study links power lines to childhood cancer. New Scientist. 2005-06-03 [2017-06-16] （American English）. 
^ John W. Farley. Power Lines and Cancer: Nothing to Fear. www.quackwatch.org. [2017-06-16]. 






 
